Now let me identify the main issue you mentioned - shipments that have been delivered (have an `actual_delivery` date) but still show an incorrect status:

{"name": "RunQuery", "arguments": {"sql": "SELECT shipment_id, tracking_number, customer_name, status, shipped_date, actual_delivery, last_updated FROM shipments WHERE actual_delivery IS NOT NULL AND status != 'Delivered' ORDER BY actual_delivery DESC"}

Let me also check for shipments that have been in transit for an unusually long time (more than 14 days) without any delivery:

{"name": "RunQuery", "arguments": {"sql": "SELECT shipment_id, tracking_number, customer_name, status, shipped_date, estimated_delivery, DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(shipped_date)) as days_in_transit FROM shipments WHERE status IN ('In Transit', 'Shipped') AND actual_delivery IS NULL AND shipped_date IS NOT NULL AND DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(shipped_date)) > 14 ORDER BY days_in_transit DESC"}

Excellent point! Let me identify those stale records based on age and status. First, let me find shipments that were created more than 7 days ago but are still stuck in pending statuses:

{"name": "RunQuery", "arguments": {"sql": "SELECT shipment_id, tracking_number, customer_name, status, created_date, shipped_date, estimated_delivery, DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(created_date)) as days_since_created, CASE WHEN shipped_date IS NOT NULL THEN DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(shipped_date)) ELSE NULL END as days_since_shipped FROM shipments WHERE status IN ('Processing', 'In Transit') AND DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(created_date)) > 7 ORDER BY days_since_created DESC"}

Now let me use a more sophisticated approach with window functions to compare against successful deliveries and establish what constitutes 'stale' behavior. I'll analyze the typical timeframes for successful deliveries to set benchmarks:

{"name": "RunQuery", "arguments": {"sql": "WITH delivery_stats AS (SELECT AVG(DATEDIFF(DATE(actual_delivery), DATE(created_date))) as avg_creation_to_delivery, AVG(DATEDIFF(DATE(actual_delivery), DATE(shipped_date))) as avg_shipping_to_delivery, MAX(DATEDIFF(DATE(actual_delivery), DATE(created_date))) as max_creation_to_delivery, MAX(DATEDIFF(DATE(actual_delivery), DATE(shipped_date))) as max_shipping_to_delivery FROM shipments WHERE actual_delivery IS NOT NULL AND shipped_date IS NOT NULL), current_shipments AS (SELECT shipment_id, tracking_number, customer_name, status, created_date, shipped_date, estimated_delivery, DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(created_date)) as days_since_created, CASE WHEN shipped_date IS NOT NULL THEN DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(shipped_date)) ELSE NULL END as days_since_shipped FROM shipments WHERE status IN ('Processing', 'In Transit', 'Shipped') AND actual_delivery IS NULL) SELECT cs.*, ds.avg_creation_to_delivery, ds.avg_shipping_to_delivery, ds.max_creation_to_delivery, ds.max_shipping_to_delivery, CASE WHEN cs.days_since_created > ds.max_creation_to_delivery THEN 'STALE - Exceeds max delivery time' WHEN cs.status = 'Processing' AND cs.days_since_created > 3 THEN 'STALE - Too long in processing' WHEN cs.status IN ('In Transit', 'Shipped') AND cs.days_since_shipped > ds.avg_shipping_to_delivery + 3 THEN 'STALE - Overdue for delivery' ELSE 'Within normal range' END as stale_assessment FROM current_shipments cs CROSS JOIN delivery_stats ds ORDER BY cs.days_since_created DESC"}

